@@TJvDriveCombo
<TITLEIMG TJvDriveCombo>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.EditsMemosAndCombos.Combos
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  A combobox that displays the available drives on the system.
Description
  Use TJvDriveCombo to display a list of available drives on the system. TJvDriveCombo derives from
  TJvCustomComboBox, exposes many of its properties and adds functionality to also display local as
  well as networked drives along with an icon representing the drive type.
See Also
  TJvDirectoryListBox, TJvDriveList, TJvFileListBox

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDriveCombo.DisplayName
Summary
  The name of the currently selected drive as presented to the user.
Description
  Use DisplayName to access the "friendly" name of the currently selected drive. If no drive is
  selected, DisplayName returns an empty string.
See Also
  TJvDriveCombo.Drive

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDriveCombo.Drive
Summary
  Specifies the currently selected drive.
Description
  Use Drive to read and change the currently selected drive. Only drives in DriveTypes are displayed
  and can be selected.
See Also
  TJvDriveCombo.DriveTypes

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDriveCombo.DriveTypes
Summary
  Specifies what drive types to show in the list.
Description
  Use DriveTypes to limit the displayed drive types in the list. Note that although you might include
  all possible drive types, only available drives will be shown.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDriveCombo.ImageSize
Summary
  Specifies the image size of the icons in the list.
Description
  Use ImageSize to specify the size of the images displayed alongside each drive. When ImageSize is
  isSmall, the drive icon is displayed to the left of the drive's display name, when ImageSize is
  isLarge, the drive icon is displayed centered above the drive's display name

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDriveCombo.Items
Summary
  Provides indexed access to all drives in the list.
Description
  Read Items to access the list of items that appears in the combo box. Although you can add new
  strings by using Items.Add etc, the effect is temporary: no drives will be affected.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDriveCombo.Offset
Summary
  Specifies how far from the left edge an item is drawn.
Description
  Use Offset to change the way an item is drawn in the list. Offset determines how many pixels at the
  left edge is skipped before the items are drawn.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDriveCombo.Refresh
Summary
  Updates the list of drives.
Description
  Call Refresh to update the display in the list. When you call Refresh, the combobox clears the
  list, scans the system for drives and fills the Items array again, finally resetting the selected
  item to be the previously selected item.

