----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDriveList.Drives
Summary
  Provides indexed access to the drives in the control.
Description
  Use Drives to access a specific drive in the list based on it's index. Valid indices range from 0 to
  DriveCount - 1. For example, when MultiSelect is true, you can use Drives and DriveCount to create
  a list of drives the user has selected:
  <AUTOLINK OFF>
  <CODE>
  var
    i:integer;
    S:string;
  begin
    S := '';
    for i := 0 to JvDriveList.DriveCount - 1 do
      if JvDriveList.Selected[i] then
        S := S + JvDriveList.Drives[i] + #13#10;
    ShowMessageFmt('You selected the following drives:'#13#10'%s',[S]);
  end; 
  </CODE>
  <AUTOLINK ON>
See Also
  TJvDriveList.DriveCount

