@@TJvFileListBox
<TITLEIMG TJvFileListBox>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.ListsAndTrees.Lists
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  A specialized list box that lists all the files in a specified directory.
Description
  Add TJvFileListBox to a form to allow users to select a file. Use TJvFileListBox along with
  TJvDriveCombo and TJvDirectoryListBox to add full file selection capabilities to a form.
See Also
  TJvDirectoryListBox, TJvDriveCombo, TJvDriveList

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFileListBox.AboutJVCL
<INCLUDE JVCL.Main.AboutJVCL.dtx>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFileListBox.Directory
Summary
  Specifies the directory that contains all the files listed in the file list box.
Description
  Set Directory to update the file list box so that it displays the files in a new directory. If the
  form includes a TJvDirectoryListBox object, set the FileList property of the directory list box to
  have the Directory property updated automatically when the user selects a new directory.
See Also
  TJvDirectoryListBox.Directory, TJvDirectoryListBox.Drive, TJvDirectoryListBox.FileList

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFileListBox.FileName
Summary
  Indicates the name of the selected file in the list box, including the path name.
Description
  Set FileName to initialize the file list box to a particular file. Read FileName to obtain the name
  of the file the user selected.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFileListBox.ForceFileExtensions
Summary
  Specifies how file extensions are displayed.
Description
  Use ForceFileExtensions to specify how file extensions are displayed. If ForceFileExtensions is
  true, file extensions are always displayed. If ForceFileExtensions is false, file extensions are
  displayed according to the user's settings in Windows Explorer.

